# Docusaurus & CI Rules

## Site Structure

- Docs plugin route base: `/` (site lives at `/agent-to-aws-guide/` on GitHub Pages)
- Sidebar defined in `sidebars.ts` — must match `SUMMARY.md` chapter list
- Landing page: `docs/index.mdx` (Guides hub with DocCard sections per Part)
- Mermaid: enabled in `docusaurus.config.ts` via `@docusaurus/theme-mermaid`
- Local search: `@easyops-cn/docusaurus-search-local`

## Adding a New Chapter

1. Create `docs/part-*/NN-slug.md` with frontmatter
2. Add doc ID to `sidebars.ts` under correct Part category
3. Add row to `SUMMARY.md` with status
4. Optionally add DocCard to `docs/index.mdx`
5. Run `npm run build` — `onBrokenLinks: 'throw'` will fail on bad links

## Part Folder Names

```
part-i-foundations/
part-ii-aws/
part-iii-containers/
part-iv-kubernetes/
part-v-infrastructure/
part-vi-ai/
part-vii-hermes/          ← NOT part-vii-ullr
preface/
appendices/
```

## CI Pipeline (`.github/workflows/book-ci.yml`)

1. Markdown lint (`.markdownlint.json`)
2. `code/scripts/ci/validate-links.sh` (docs/, resources/labs/, root meta files)
3. `npm run build`
4. Deploy to GitHub Pages on push to `main`

## Do Not

- Enable blog plugin (disabled intentionally)
- Change `baseUrl` without updating all absolute `/agent-to-aws-guide/` paths
- Commit `build/`, `.docusaurus/`, or `node_modules/`
